- Not gonna happen.

242
00:17:46,407 --> 00:17:47,694
Never.

243
00:17:47,951 --> 00:17:49,896
You don't have to be so blunt.

244
00:17:49,936 --> 00:17:52,422
Because it ain't happening. No way.

245
00:17:52,509 --> 00:17:54,939
Could it be that maybe...

246
00:17:55,320 --> 00:18:01,407
Isn't she coming on to me?
That's gotta be it, right?

247
00:18:02,399 --> 00:18:06,563
Could it be that maybe...
Could it be that maybe...

248
00:18:12,017 --> 00:18:13,757
That's gotta be it, right?

249
00:18:21,570 --> 00:18:23,258
I'm home.

250
00:18:27,245 --> 00:18:28,450
What are you making?

251
00:18:28,792 --> 00:18:30,825
I just went shopping.

252
00:18:31,683 --> 00:18:33,590
You were hanging out with Midori, right?

253
00:18:33,630 --> 00:18:34,882
Don't lie to me.

254
00:18:35,193 --> 00:18:37,320
Taro couldn't wait anymore, so I made udon.

255
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:38,704
This will be the dinner.

256
00:18:39,319 --> 00:18:40,933
Hey, move. You're in the way.

257
00:18:41,415 --> 00:18:46,281
Alright, Taro, udon's ready.
Here you go, sorry for the wait.

258
00:18:46,881 --> 00:18:50,334
Midori sent me a message saying
we should let Mina and Taro play together.

259
00:18:50,430 --> 00:18:52,544
Taro, you sure? I bought chicken.

260
00:18:52,550 --> 00:18:54,368
Yeah. I like udon.

261
00:18:54,408 --> 00:18:59,315
Also, get the iPad out. I promised
Taro extra time 'cause he worked hard today.

262
00:18:59,570 --> 00:19:02,887
Don't make promises like that
without telling me. How would I know?

263
00:19:02,892 --> 00:19:06,476
What are you talking about?
I sent you a message. Check it.

264
00:19:06,492 --> 00:19:08,965
You're the one sending me
crap messages all the time.

265
00:19:09,335 --> 00:19:13,595
And I told you, stop trying
to drag Taro out against his will.

266
00:19:13,635 --> 00:19:15,562
You put pressure on him.

267
00:19:15,602 --> 00:19:18,363
I'm not pressuring anyone.

268
00:19:24,033 --> 00:19:28,972
Is it okay to just give him
more iPad time so easily?

269
00:19:28,982 --> 00:19:31,487
You do the same thing when it suits you.

270
00:19:31,615 --> 00:19:35,122
Taro, Mama's gonna take a bath.
Before Daddy and I start fighting.

271
00:19:35,162 --> 00:19:36,180
Okay, sure.

272
00:19:36,220 --> 00:19:38,288
Saying it like that is what starts a fight.

273
00:19:38,328 --> 00:19:39,997
No, it's not.

274
00:19:40,831 --> 00:19:45,729
Stop lecturing Taro. He worked hard
at Sunflower today. Right, Taro?

275
00:19:50,747 --> 00:19:54,133
Taro, are you sure? Just udon?

276
00:19:55,497 --> 00:19:57,630
Daddy'll make you some yummy chicken.

277
00:19:57,670 --> 00:20:00,055
No, I'm fine. I love udon.

278
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:09,046
Taro, Mina was sad, you know.

279
00:20:09,183 --> 00:20:12,690
You should meet your friends
at times like this. They would be happy, too.

280
00:20:13,170 --> 00:20:16,313
Mama told you to stop
lecturing me about stuff.

281
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:18,468
Daddy gets to say things, too.

282
00:20:20,098 --> 00:20:21,343
I'll tell Mama.

283
00:20:22,412 --> 00:20:26,352
That would make you a meanie.
You wanna be a meanie?

284
00:20:26,869 --> 00:20:30,166
You're the meanie, Dad. Stop talking to me.

285
00:20:30,282 --> 00:20:35,336
Nope, can't do that. I want you
to make more friends, Taro.

286
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,822
Dad doesn't wanna say this stuff either.

287
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:47,038
I'm in my stable stage, so here's the news.
Taro's getting another cousin.

288
00:20:47,294 --> 00:20:50,622
We're happily expecting our second child!

289
00:20:50,655 --> 00:20:54,796
Mom and Dad are coming next week,
so you guys should come hang out, too.

290
00:20:57,161 --> 00:21:00,675
Taro, Haruta's mom is having a baby.

291
00:21:02,631 --> 00:21:05,204
You're getting another cousin.
Aren't you happy?

292
00:21:05,637 --> 00:21:06,661
Not really.

293
00:21:06,701 --> 00:21:12,138
"Not really?" You like Haruta, right?
You're getting another cousin!

294
00:21:13,302 --> 00:21:16,239
I'd rather join the Doburock fan club.

295
00:21:16,945 --> 00:21:19,255
That's only if you go to school every day.

296
00:21:23,050 --> 00:21:24,311
A second kid...

297
00:21:27,189 --> 00:21:31,124
You know, if you ever made it big...

298
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:34,011
I'd be fine with having like four kids.

299
00:21:34,051 --> 00:21:36,998
Huh? Isn't four a bit much?

300
00:21:37,038 --> 00:21:40,490
What? It'd be fun. A big, lively family.

301
00:21:41,109 --> 00:21:44,263
With our genes,
they'd probably all be adorable.

302
00:21:44,441 --> 00:21:49,421
Yeah. I mean, we do have
the looks going for us.

303
00:21:49,461 --> 00:21:51,709
Right, the looks at least.

304
00:21:52,895 --> 00:21:56,200
Oh stop. Why are we so silly?

305
00:22:01,035 --> 00:22:02,508
Let's do it one more time.

306
00:22:03,025 --> 00:22:04,241
Sure.

307
00:22:14,753 --> 00:22:15,753
Next Episode Preview

308
00:22:15,778 --> 00:22:17,535
Why don't you two have another one?

309
00:22:17,575 --> 00:22:19,672
There's no way. Not for us.

310
00:22:19,712 --> 00:22:21,421
Always dropping bombs, huh, Mom?

311
00:22:21,461 --> 00:22:22,720
Enough. Cut it out.

312
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:24,813
Oh, we got an email from your wife.

313
00:22:24,922 --> 00:22:26,738
Why do you pull stuff like that?

314
00:22:26,779 --> 00:22:29,321
Now I wanna sleep with you
even less than before.
